cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.GR, cs.CY, cs.SI 

The paper discusses a cyber security threat (phishing) and proposes a serious game as a solution to enhance user confidence in mitigating such attacks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Computer Science focused on Cybersecurity (cs.CR). Additionally, the game design approach and the use of persuasive design principles suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) and Graphics (cs.GR). The empirical study conducted to identify key elements of the game interface suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of Cybernetics (cs.CY) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
